edu.umw.cpsc.humantrafficking
Class Victim

java.lang.Object
  edu.umw.cpsc.humantrafficking.Victim
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, sim.engine.Steppable
public class Victim
extends java.lang.Object
implements sim.engine.Steppable

A Victim represents a woman being abducted for sex trafficking. Every individual woman in the simulation is represented as a Victim object, even if that individual is not currently a victim (e.g., she may have escaped.)

setLocation

possiblyEscape

public void possiblyEscape()
Take into account a victim's chance of escape and decide whether they do escape this year. If so, sets their status to "escapee".

possiblyRetire

public void possiblyRetire()
This function takes into account a victim's age and, if older than 30, randomly determines whether they should be removed from the system.

step

public void step(sim.engine.SimState state)
Perform actions for this Victim this year. Victims are scheduled to run on July 1st of each year. Their step() includes the following items:
  1. Decide whether this victim escapes from forced prostitution.
  2. Decide whether this victim "retires" (i.e., is determined to be too old for forced prostitution, and dumped from the system.

Specified by:
step in interface sim.engine.Steppable
Parameters:
state - the HumanTrafficking simulation.
